	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Sometimes if the 4 screws that hold that part down are too tight or too loose, it won't work.  Chances are, they just need to be adjusted.  Pretty easy job, really.  
<br />
<br />Remove that part and see if it still works externally.  Once you get a look at the mechanism of how it locks down and pops back up, you should be able to tell if it is still in working condition.  I've never actually seen one of these failed before.
<br />
<br />-Rob

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


